reviews.review: I didn't really care for the movie and I love Star Wars. Of the 9 in the main storyline, I would place this as #5 at best.
This was such a great addition to the Star Wars series!! I laughed and cried! I will definitely be watching this movie again and again!

As a life long Star Wars fan I had a tough time getting into this movie. Could it be fatigue from how disappointing Last Jedi was for me or this installments lack of creativity and storytelling? Found myself too many times shaking my head thinking how they "borrowed" this scene or that one from the original. I wanted to enjoy this movie but in the end the story felt rushed, unresolved, and unsatisfying for me.
Liked movie very much. Some of it was to predictable but it was still not a sleeper. Sorry to see it all end.
Movie was too fast paced, took some easy ways out story wise.
Like the Star Wars movies. This one and the last one were a little too cheesy for me.

Good closure of the series.  The beginning was a little disjointed and the events immediately after the final battle ended were a little over-the-top for me.  But all in all, a good flick with a good story and plenty of action.  And Billy Dee as Lando is still the man.
good ending, probably more of a 3 or 4 star movie, but since it was star wars and the final chapter, went higher

For some unknown reason everyone is Listening to the critics which is odd because most critics are morons and every one knows that when it comes to Joker or Terminator dark fate but when it come to the rise of Skywalker their word is gospel. This movie is not that bad it is way better than last Jedi it has a decent story. Its not perfect and yes Rei is still a stupid character but its still a good movie. All my friends and family loved it and I really enjoyed it. Go see it and don't listen to the critics.
The movie lacked causation. The trilogy lacked planning. Disney just knew the Star Wars faithful would eat up everything they put out.
